# 8. 届けたい音色

Ichika's Song: ♪————
Miku: <*Nod* This really is a wonderful song...>
Miku: <All that's left is to hear what the others have to say after they listen to it today.>
Ichika: R-Right...
Miku: <Are you nervous, Ichika?>
Ichika: O-Of course I am. This is the first actual song I've written.
Ichika: Also, Saki always writes these amazing songs for us, so I'm worried that it's going to pale in comparison...
Miku: <I don't think you have anything to worry about. Music isn't about comparing yourself to others.>
Miku: <Listening to your song, Ichika, I got a clear sense of what sort of message you were trying to send. So, I think it's fine the way it is...>
Ichika: Miku...
Ichika: Thank goodness. I'm so glad I asked you to join me today, Miku. It's like the first time I showed everyone my lyrics. I'm so nervous...
Saki's Voice: Whoa! It's already this late?! Sorry for making you help me with that stuff!
Ichika: Oh...
Miku: <Sounds like they're here. Good luck, Ichika...>
Saki: Ichi! Sorry for being so late! The teacher asked me to do some stuff and...!
Ichika: H-Hello, everyone.
Shiho: Hm? Miku's here too?
Miku: <We were having a little chat.>
Saki: You were? About what?
Ichika: Oh... U-Uhh...
Ichika: S-So... There's something I need to ask all of you...
Honami: *Gasp* Does this mean...?
Saki: Huh?! What's going on?! Oh, is this about the new pancake place that just opened up near school?! I've been thinking we should check it out, too!
Shiho: I seriously doubt it, Saki, so please be quiet for a bit.
Ichika: H-Haha... The thing is... Um...
Ichika: I wrote my own song, and I want you all to listen to it.
Shiho: Your own song...?
Shiho: You wrote one, Ichika?
Ichika: Yeah...
Saki: What?! Ichi, you wrote a song?!
Saki: That's so awesome! I had no idea that you were working on one! I really wanna hear it!
Honami: I see. It's finally done... I'm so happy for you, Ichika!
Saki: Wait, Hona, you knew...?
Honami: Oh, um... Yes... I happened to walk in on Ichika working on it...
Saki: What?! Why didn't you tell us?!
Ichika: Please don't blame her. I wanted to have you all listen to it when it was complete, so I asked her to keep it a secret until then.
Miku: <Hehe...>
Saki: Wait a sec... That giggle... Miku, you knew too, didn't you?
Miku: <Yes, I did. However, I only heard about it yesterday.>
Saki: No fair! No fair! Lemme listen to it!
Shiho: I'd like to hear your song as well, Ichika.
Ichika: O-Of course. That's why I brought it up. I am a little nervous... But I want to hear your honest opinions.
Ichika: So... I'll play it now.
Saki: Oh wow...
Saki: This song's super duper amazingly good! How do I put it...?
Saki: It's so you, Ichi! There's so much warmth... And so much kindness in the lyrics. It's like you're saying you'll be there when I really need you.
Shiho: Yeah, it's like I'm being wrapped in a warm blanket... And I really like how it captures you so well, Ichika.
Ichika: Thanks, you two...!
Miku: <I didn't realize that's how you saw her, Shiho.>
Shiho: H-Hey, I was just trying to give my impression, that's all.
Honami: Miku's voice is also really beautiful. It goes so well with the song... Actually, Ichika, this Miku kind of reminds me of you.
Ichika: Wait, Miku...reminds you of me...?
Honami: Yes, it's like... Your feelings and her feelings have become one, you know?
Honami: Just through Miku's voice, you make it clear that you care about her very much.
Ichika: R-Right...
Ichika: Thank you...
Saki: Hey, but you sorta just made this for fun, right, Ichi...?
Saki: I was thinking I kinda wanna play it as Leo/need. How would you feel about that?
Ichika: ...!
Honami: I'd like to play it as well. I was really wondering how it'd sound if we did.
Shiho: You had that in mind when you wrote it, didn't you Ichika? I mean, it uses the same instruments we do, and your message... It all feels like Leo/need.
Ichika: Yes, Shiho. That's right...
Saki: That means...!
Ichika: If you're all okay with it... I'd like for us to play this song as Leo/need.
Saki: Of course we're okay with it! I mean, Ichi, it's your debut as a songwriter♪
Honami: Oh, I have a suggestion regarding that...
Honami: For this song, why don't we have a video of us playing it and a separate one using this Miku version?
Honami: The way she sings it is so beautiful that I feel like it'd be a waste to not include her somehow.
Ichika: So, two videos...? One of us performing and another of Miku singing?
Saki: I think that'd be great! I personally really love Miku videos. I watch them all the time!
Shiho: Yeah, also...
Shiho: Plenty of other people like Miku, so we may be able to reach more people by making a video with her in it.
Ichika: Miku's voice is going to help my song reach all those people...?
Miku: I also want lots and lots of people in your world to hear the song you and her created, Ichika...
Miku: This song, your thoughts, your feelings, this melody... The people who need it most are going to be so touched by them all.
Ichika: (Miku...)
Ichika: Right...
Ichika: I want it to reach as many people as possible too.
Ichika: Our song... With Miku!
???: *Sigh* I come all the way out to a live house when I'm supposed to have the day off, and... Another swing and a miss.
???: To be fair, it's not exactly easy to find a diamond in the rough. In terms of that...
???: That show was something else.
???: But there's no information out there about that band. I figured that high school kids would be posting videos and stuff online, but...
???: When I checked after the show, they didn't even seem to have any channels set up... Hm?
???: Wait, this is...!
???: Four subscribers... So, the four of them? Did they just set up this channel?
???: Hey, they even posted a Miku song...
???: Leo/need... Seems I'll need to keep an eye on them.
